The paper deals with the problem of channel state information acquisition in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the calibration of RF hardware asymmetry, which is related to system control and optimization (cs.SY). The use of antenna grouping to improve calibration accuracy and speed is a technique that falls under the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
